Who We Serve





























Who We Serve

Individuals, couples and families

Investors seeking to grow their incomes

Those with a minimum of $ 1.5 million of investable assets








Sample Client Profile: Accumulating Assets

Working professional

Business Owner

Long investment horizon


These clients are working full-time, building wealth for eventual retirement.  The cash flow generated in the portfolios of this type of client is usually reinvested to build additional income.

  




Sample Client Profile: Taking Distributions

Retiree

Widowed


These are clients who are living off the money generated by their investments. As a result, their investment strategy might be more conservative and instead of reinvesting all of the cash flow produced in their portfolio, they will take a certain amount of that income in the form of distributions.
  




Sample Client Profile: Money in Transition

Divorced

Sold a business

Inherited wealth


These clients might have accumulated assets quickly through a business transaction or life changing event. They may intend to live off a portion of this wealth, while also investing for the future. 
  











About Us / Working With Northstar





























Working With Northstar


Watch Our Video to Learn More







Northstar approaches business differently. We provide our clients with individualized attention, in-house technical expertise and a transparent fee structure that ties our success to that of our clients. 
Here is a closer look at what separates us from the competition:  

“Reputation is built up over many, many years of actually doing what you say you’re going to do and indeed, putting clients’ interests ahead of anything else.”
-Bob Van Wetter





Fiduciary Standard
As a registered investment advisor, Northstar operates under a fiduciary standard of care.  This means you are working with professionals who are dedicated to doing what’s in your best interest. 








Fee Only Advisor 
Northstar is also a fee only advisor, which means the only compensation Northstar receives for managing client portfolios are the investment advisory fees paid directly by our clients.  

Fees are based on the size of the client’s portfolio, and are generally paid on a quarterly basis.  
Northstar’s fees are directly related to how well we help our clients grow and protect their wealth.  We believe the fee-only relationship places us in direct partnership with our clients.
Money managed by Northstar is held by third-party custodians – usually large, national companies who provide our clients with a high level of security at very low costs. The third party custodian arrangement creates an important layer of protection for our clients as there is always an independent valuation of their assets.

 




Team Management 
When you work with Northstar, you have a relationship with our entire firm.  

A committee comprised of the principals of our firm and the firm’s portfolio managers oversee, research and set all of our investment strategies.
Clients work with a primary portfolio manager, who is responsible for the management of their accounts.  We also assign secondary portfolio managers to clients, so there are always two managers who are familiar with each portfolio.  
A team of service professionals is dedicated to the timely and accurate completion of the tasks needed to operate and service our clients’ portfolios. We pride ourselves on taking great care of our clients and their families. 















About Us / Values





























Our Values







You should work with a firm whose values about money reflect your values about money. At Northstar, we value careful, prudent and balanced solutions to money and wealth management. Here are some of the other tenets we value:


 
Trust. Successful investment advisory relationships are based on trust. You should know that investment advisors are required to adhere to a rigorous fiduciary standard of care when managing client assets. A core principle of the fiduciary standard is that investment advisors must put their clients’ interests first. At Northstar, we take this obligation seriously. We work hard to live up to our clients’ expectations every day.
Independence. You should expect your investment advisors to be independent and to form their own opinions about what investments are prudent and in the best interests of clients. Our belief is that independence comes from our ownership structure. Because the principals of Northstar own and operate the firm, we answer only to our clients and ourselves. We have purposely chosen this business structure so that we can deliver independent advice to you.
Expertise. Northstar is led by a team that understands the risk and return parameters of the financial markets and can offer prudent and careful guidance. You can review our backgrounds, education, credentials and writings to get a sense of our competence. In your interviews with us, see how we answer and explain our strategy. Does it make sense to you and do we have a command of what we are doing? We certainly believe we do, and strive to serve as leaders in our industry.




 
Responsiveness. As an independent advisory firm, we pride ourselves on providing direct, personal service to our clients. Our goal is to respond to client requests promptly, and to provide a high level of personal service through our Northstar team. 
Transparent Fees. Northstar is a fee-only advisor, meaning that the compensation we receive comes from the investment advisory fees we charge our clients. We do not receive commissions or outside compensation. Our fees are clear, transparent and competitive in our industry.
 
 
 














